[{"id":"VR794085","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two blocks attached to either end of a light string that passes over a circular wheel of mass m. The block on the left has mass m sub 1, and the block on the right has mass m sub 2. The tension in the left portion of the string is T sub 1, and the tension in the right portion of the string is T sub 2. The block with mass m sub 1 is lower than the block with mass m sub 2.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR794085.g03.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two blocks of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub 1\"><math alttext=\"m sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub 2\"><math alttext=\"m sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> are connected by a thin string that passes over a circular wheel of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span>, as shown. The wheel is attached to a vertical stand and rotates freely about its center. The string does not slip on the wheel and exerts forces <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> on the blocks. When the wheel is released from rest in the position shown, it undergoes an angular acceleration and rotates clockwise. Which of the following statements about the magnitudes of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> is correct?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR794085_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1 equals T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1 equals T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> because the tension in the string must always be constant within the string.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1 equals T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1 equals T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> because both blocks have the same acceleration.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1 is less than T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1 is less than T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> because <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub 1\"><math alttext=\"m sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> is farther from the wheel than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub 2\"><math alttext=\"m sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1 is less than T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1 is less than T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> because an unbalanced clockwise torque is needed to accelerate the wheel clockwise.</p>"],"answer":3}]